                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s1"><span class="num">01</span> Introduction</h3>
                    <p>Auto ISP Billing (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;our,&rdquo; or &ldquo;us&rdquo;) is committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our ISP billing and management software platform.</p>
                    <p>By using Auto ISP Billing, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our services.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s2"><span class="num">02</span> Information we collect</h3>
                    <p>We collect several types of information to provide and improve our services:</p>
                    <h4>2.1 Personal information</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Account information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, company details, billing address</li>
                        <li><strong>Customer data:</strong> Customer names, addresses, contact information, service plans, payment history</li>
                        <li><strong>Payment information:</strong> Credit card details, bank account information, UPI IDs (processed securely through payment gateways)</li>
                        <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP addresses, browser type, device information, login timestamps</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>2.2 Usage information</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Service usage patterns and bandwidth consumption</li>
                        <li>Transaction history and billing records</li>
                        <li>Support tickets and communication logs</li>
                        <li>System logs and error reports</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>2.3 Network integration data</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>MikroTik router configurations and connection logs</li>
                        <li>RADIUS server authentication records</li>
                        <li>Network performance metrics</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s-mobile"><span class="num">02b</span> Mobile app permissions (Android)</h3>
                    <p>The <strong>AutoISP Billing</strong> Android application
                    (package <code>com.autoispbilling.mobile</code>) requests
                    the following runtime permissions. Each permission maps to
                    a specific feature; if you deny it, only that feature is
                    affected and the rest of the app continues to work normally.</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>CAMERA:</strong> Capture photographs of customer ID proof for KYC, installed network hardware, and physical payment receipts that you attach to complaint tickets.</li>
                        <li><strong>ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION / ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION / ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION / FOREGROUND_SERVICE_LOCATION:</strong> Used <em>only by field-engineer accounts</em> to record where on-site work was performed and to dispatch the nearest engineer. Customer accounts do not transmit location.</li>
                        <li><strong>RECORD_AUDIO:</strong> Powers the in-app speed-test diagnostic. Audio is processed locally on the device and never uploaded to our servers.</li>
                        <li><strong>BLUETOOTH / BLUETOOTH_SCAN / BLUETOOTH_CONNECT:</strong> Pair with thermal Bluetooth receipt printers used by admin and sub-LCO accounts to print payment receipts.</li>
                        <li><strong>POST_NOTIFICATIONS:</strong> Deliver bill reminders, ticket status updates and service alerts.</li>
                        <li><strong>USE_BIOMETRIC / USE_FINGERPRINT:</strong> Faster sign-in via fingerprint or face unlock. The biometric template never leaves your phone &mdash; the app only stores a flag indicating that you have enabled biometric login.</li>
                        <li><strong>READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE / WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE:</strong> Save downloaded PDF invoices and receipts to your phone's storage so you can view them offline.</li>
                        <li><strong>INTERNET:</strong> Required to communicate with the AutoISP Billing servers over HTTPS.</li>
                        <li><strong>VIBRATE / SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW:</strong> Subtle haptic feedback and on-screen tooltips for the speed-test overlay.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>You may revoke any permission at any time from
                    <em>Android Settings &rarr; Apps &rarr; AutoISP Billing &rarr;
                    Permissions</em>. The app does <strong>not</strong> use any
                    third-party advertising SDK, does <strong>not</strong> read
                    your contacts, SMS, call logs, photo gallery or files
                    outside its own folder, and does <strong>not</strong>
                    collect the Android Advertising ID.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="policy-section"><h3 id="s3"><span class="num">03</span> How we use your information</h3>
                    <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
                    <ul>
